description: Wolverine Noir TPB (2010). Promotional info - "Wolverine Noir (2010) (Digital TPB) English | CBR | 97 pages | 135.94 MB The Bowery, 1937. Jim Logan, the fiercest knife expert in New York, runs a seedy detective agency called "LOGAN & LOGAN"...along with his useless, halfwit brother, Dog. They're the best they are at what they do. But when a swanky dame named Mariko Yashida struts into the office, she opens up a world of hurt for Logan, forcing him to revisit his painful, bloody past. The latest in the Marvel Noir series, Wolverine Noir reunites the acclaimed Wolverine team of Stuart Moore (Iron Man) and C.P. Smith (The Programme). Collects Wolverine Noir #1-4."
